          "Chaplain in WW II, survivor of Pearl Harbor with the help of their sire. Ruthelessly ensures the needs of the pack above all others."
        ],
        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "Your memory of your mortal life is hazy and remote.  You know you were a chaplain in the navy.  You remember the sound of bombs falling and the feel of your flesh tearing.  You remember fire, and the ocean water cooling and stinging.    According to your sire, his pack of dolphins collected you as a sacrifice, and he chose to dedicate your life to Caine instead of devour you because of the words you spoke.  You cannot remember these words, and he would not tell you.  Perhaps Caine spoke through you?  Your sire kept haven below the waves, and while he was able to wear aware your humanity, he could not teach you a new path.  Frustrated, he cast you upon the shore, virtually at the feet of a pack.  You had learned what it was to be Cainite at the bottom of the sea, but from that pack, you learned what it was to be Sabbat.  When Non Propter Se needed members, you volunteered.  The first time your pod passed near your Sire's haven, you visited him.  The meeting was odd, to say the least, but he sent a dolphin with you when you returned to the air and your pod.  Oh, and your name?  You're fairly sure it's yours because of the dog tags you had when you were returned to the land by your sire, but sometimes you wonder."
        ],
